Inspired by [Python 3.9's `removeprefix` and `removesuffix`](https://dev.to/delta456/python-removeprefix-and-removesuffix-34jp).

These methods are different from `trim{Start|End}` because `remove{Prefix|Suffix}` will only remove if the string starts with the specified substring:

```js
_.trimStart('-_-abc-_-', '_-');
// => 'abc-_-'

_.removePrefix('-_-abc-_-', '_-');
// => '-_-abc-_-'
```

Another difference is that `remove{Prefix|Suffix}` has a second mandatory parameter, where trim's methods default to `whitespace`.

